These results show that ECs are split on their feelings about inter-Reserve support.
When a Tukey HSD post hoc cluster analysis was run on the data to determine if different groups of ECs emerged with varied preferences, three groups formed.
Group 3 has significantly higher means for each answer than the other two groups.
Group 3 (consisting of eleven Reserves) indicates that they are interested in working with other Reserves to improve programs.
The remaining Reserves have less interest in working together nationally.
Members of group 3 consistently rate the 7, 8, 9, or 10 responses (Table 15).
