The reserve staff provides teachers with curriculum and sampling equipment, they visit classrooms for presentations on water quality issues, teach students to use test equipment in the lab and in the field and they select sample sites to monitor and then submit their findings to the Reserve.
MARE (Marine Activities Resources and Education)--MARE is an interdisciplinary K-8 whole school change program that engages teachers, students, parents, administrators, and the community to transform elementary and middle schools into dynamic laboratories for the study of the ocean.
MARE is a supplemental curriculum, designed to enrich science instruction for all students while promoting equity, language acquisition and academic excellence among English language learners.
The MARE curriculum focuses each grade level on a different ocean habitat.
Individual teachers at MARE schools use the thematic curriculum at their own pace throughout the year as a
