Sapelo Island NERR, Georgia One, two, and three-day programs can be arranged for groups of 10-30 teachers.
Instruction and materials highlight the ecology and wildlife of 4th-8th barrier island systems (estuarine, upland and beach habitats) as well as the history of Sapelo Island.
Presentation, guided walk, hands-on activities, workshop, investigation/research
Coastal/Barrier Island Ecology
120-150
South Slough NERR, Oregon MARE has been adopted by the local Coos Bay School District as their science curriculum.
We have been working with a partnership to promote development of a teacher training institute for MARE while conducting training for MARE teachers.
Teachers participate with parent volunteers in 4-6 hours of training on-site to gain background knowledge in estuary ecology and the delivery of site based curricula.
Presentation, guided walk, hands-on activities, investigation/research
